Path: README.md
...
 95	
 96	```ts
 97	import { RestateIngressClient } from 'deepkit-restate';
 98	
 99	const client = new RestateIngressClient({ url: 'http://localhost:9080' });
 100	```
 101	
 102	Or retrieve the configured instance via DI:
 103	
 104	```ts
 105	const client = app.get<RestateClient>();
 106	```
 107	
 108	### Using the Client
 109	
 110	To create a proxy to a **service**:
 111	
 112	```ts
 113	const user = client.service<UserServiceApi>();
 114	```
 115	
 116	To create a proxy to an **object**:
 117	
 118	```ts
 119	const user = client.object<UserObjectApi>();
 120	```
 121	
 122	### Invoking Methods
 123	
 124	Durable request (waits for a result):
 125	
 126	```ts
 127	await client.call(user.create());
 128	```
 129	
 130	Fire-and-forget (does not wait for result):
 131	
 132	```ts
 133	await client.send(user.create());
 134	```
 135	
 136	You can configure delivery options:
 137	
 138	```ts
 139	await client.send(user.create(), { delay: '10s' });
 140	```
...
 410	
 411	## Awakeables
 412	
 413	Awakeables are special constructs to **wait for asynchronous external events**. They provide a promise you can `await` to pause saga execution until an event occurs.
 414	
 415	Create awakeables with the saga context inside your saga methods:
 416	
 417	```ts
 418	this.confirmTicketAwakeable = this.ctx.awakeable<TicketConfirmed>();
 419	```
 420	
 421	---
 422	
 423	## Using the Saga Context
 424	
 425	The `RestateSagaContext` (`this.ctx`) provides utilities like:
 426	
 427	- `awakeable<T>()`: Creates an awakeable to wait for events.
 428	- `set<T>(key, value)`: Persist state data during saga execution.
 429	- `get<T>(key)`: Retrieve persisted state.
 430	
 431	---
 432	
 433	## Calling Other Services
 434	
 435	All service calls inside invocation handlers automatically use the underlying `client.call`. This means:
...
